text:
Hey, you know how everyone already hates me for a thing today? Time to double down!
~James, probably.
His and my ratios on the tweets during the shitstorm were better than Saff and Wedge's. People know we're right, or they're dumb
Like "the only possible way a leak could have happened is if someone spoiled an entire sheet and no other possibility exists" dumb
I don’t really have a stake in the conversation. I just think it’s pretty ballsy to see the reaction he originally got and then tweet this.
I don't know if it's ballsy as much as "What do you people expect me to do?"

I knew cards in this set and didn't say anything because I figured it's my valuable info and I'm not sharing it for free, but he came to a different conclusion since you'd have to have Back to Basics already to benefit from the intel
So am I right in saying you agree with his justification, but not how he’s handling the current situation?

I don't think he should have run his mouth off in the first place, but I think it's fine to laugh at dipshits who are talking about "insider trading" and calling for Channel Fireball to be investigated or the DCI to ban him
Ah, okay. Fair enough.
I'm being a little aggro about it, but the whole thing is stupid. Wedge, Prof and Saffron all peddle outrage for youtube clicks and I'm a little sick of it
Yeah, I agree with that.
I’m outraged.
WORKS AS DESIGNED
Iunno, just seems like trying to fight through the perception is pointless. Or at least not worth it. Perception is reality right?
People think “insider trading” so that’s what it is now.
Arguing against it just looks like a cover up.
Actually, if you’re peddling, I’ll take 3 quarts of outrage, 2 lbs of pique, and ummmm...5 slices of tizzy.
Wedge, Saf and the Prof use the same playbook as Hambly, just using X's instead of O's
I’m glad I’m not the only one who feels that way. Ever since my interaction with Wedge over the military care packages.

Catching up on the conversation, this is fun to watch as a bystander. The folks acting like it's insider trading are almost as insane, probably moreso actually, than the people saying that the professor is responsible for boxes of the set being sold under MSRP
You know, I’m kinda shocked he didn’t own that one.
The professor?
Yeah. Seems like a thing he’d jokingly take credit for.
"jokingly"
I mean, that’s conditioning, yeah?

I don't so much mind wedge. I used to lump him in with that caste of content folks but I think after his back injury and dealing with Hambly's weird obsession he's become much more accessible to the random person he interacts with
Speaking of douche conditioning, Trump asked a bunch of soldiers if they’d take a pay cut to pay for the wall. When no one said yeah, he called them bad Americans.
wut....
